ABUJA – Protesters on Friday stormed Upper Area Court located in Zuba in the Federal Capital Ter­ritory (FCT ) Abuja calling on the court to ensure justice is served on Jaruma. Speaking on behalf of the group, Johnson Kolawole Miche­al as ked the court to imposemax­imum punishment on Jaruma to serve as a deterrent to others. According to him “The time when people can just get up from their sleep and concoct lies against well-meaning Nigerians is gone. 100 Shops Built On DSC Land Brought Down In Udu Alao-Akala To Be Buried On February 18 “Until someone is used as a scapegoat, people will not un­derstand the extent of our laws and in this very case, she must face the consequences. “We are also calling on all Ni­gerians to stop patronising her, she is a scam and she uses the medium for blackmail”. The trial Judge, Ismailia Ab­dullahi, while ruling on the bail application admitted Jaruma to bail with one surety who must be a civil servant of grade level 12 working within the FCT. The court also restrained her from making any further social media posts or comments and cautioned parties to maintain the status quo on the matter. The judge said “The court did not remand her in custody as a punitive means to penalise the defendant but to make her present and answer to her case. By this I shall quick to point out that the charge against the defendant is bailable but not ordinary. POLL “I here by granter bail on the following condition of a surety who must be a grade level 12 working with in the FCT. Also, all the parties involved in the case should stay from anything that would be prejudicial to the case.” Recall that Jaruma was re­manded in Suleja prison after she pleaded not guilty to charges of cyber stalking preferred against her.